+An Engram remains an Engram only when it preserves the durable-record invariants:
+it is durable, content-addressed, lineage-bearing, decayed, provenance-stamped, and may
+optionally carry attestation. Those invariants define the durable medium; they do not apply
+to transient Pulses until a Pulse is graduated.
+
 The name "Engram" comes from neuroscience: a hypothetical means by which memories are stored
 as biophysical changes in the brain (Semon 1904; Lashley 1950; Tonegawa et al. 2015, Science
 348(6238)). In Roko, an Engram is the digital equivalent — a content-addressed unit of
 cognition that persists, decays, and can be retrieved by similarity or query.
 
+For the Pulse sibling medium and the graduation boundary between live transport and durable
